<activity><title>Solving Inequalities Graphically</title>

<task><p>Solve <m>2x+1 \lt 7</m>.</p>

        <commentary audience="instructor"><title>Note</title>
        <p> Point out that <m>2x+1 \lt 7</m> is the same as <m>y \lt 7</m>, so we are looking for <m>x</m>-values that produce points on the graph with <m>y</m>-coordinate less than 7.</p></commentary>

    <sidebyside widths="60% 40%">
    <p><ol>   
    <li><p><m>\blert{\text{Find the point on the graph with y = 7.}}</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\blert{\text{Which points on the graph have}}</m></p>
         <p><m>\blert{\text{y-coordinates less than 7?}}</m></p></li> 
    <li><p><m>\blert{\text{Shade those points.}}</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\blert{\text{Drop straight down from the marked}}</m></p> 
        <p><m>\blert{\text{points to the x-axis.}}</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\blert{\text{Shade that portion of the x-axis.}}</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\blert{\text{Write your solution as an inequality.}}</m></p></li>
</ol></p>
<image source="act-1-2-3.png"></image></sidebyside>
</task>

